content.description: Starts on pockets, and through to a rail for the first clip. The crux is between the 2nd and 3rd bolt with a shallow crimp.
content.protection: Four bolts, with carabiners on anchors.
content.location: Just to right of a large hueco/cave between Captain Hook, and Orange Huecos.

content.description: Follow the textured rock bolt to bolt about vertical, and the route lessens just after the hole hold.
content.protection: As of 1/16/21, the bolts on this route and the neighboring 5.8 were missing.
content.location: The second route you will see approaching from the boat ramp. This is just left of a corner in the rock. The surface is rough in texture and a hold that is a slab with a handhold sized hole in it might catch your eye.

content.description: This is a largely vertical face climb that starts with mantling a giant ledge, then go bolt to bolt for the first two bolts, then for the rating go left at the second bolt to make a few moves to gain the lip, traverse the lip right to clip the anchors. It looks like it used to be easier and more direct, there are some rock scars where some blocks broke off. Watch for people tossing things off the deck above, and as always don't top out.
content.protection: Two bolts on the route, the anchors are two bolts, one with a carabiner attached, the hangers are not rappel hangers. Never trust your life to one piece of gear.
content.location: The first bolst you will see headed in from the boat ramp. This is directly under a deck at the resort.

content.description: Super good route that trends right into the wide black streak.  Be careful on the second clip, decking looks possible.
Pull out the horizontal roof into thin pockets and to the top.
Start to right of Whitey. Climb through the orange huecos and to the bulge. If you find LOTS of bird droppings over the bulge, you are on the right route.
content.protection: Four bolts, anchors have carabiners already.
content.location: Two routes to the right of Captain Hook. Also the last route to the right on the ledge.

content.description: Overhanging gray pods and pockets into the alcove below the roof.  Hard last clip.
Epic route with dynamic movements. The crux is about 3/4 the way up throwing from a undercling to a cresent shaped crip.
content.location: Climb onto the left most ledge. The route starts beneath a very large hueco/cave.

content.description: Move right from the second bolt on Anglo Saxon.
Located on the right side of the wall, traverse out of the roof to the right, then past a single bolt to the anchor.

Things get serious right when you pull off the ground. Start with a tough boulder problem and then continue up the steep arete passing tweaky pockets, slopers, and even a mono wrap. Powerful with big moves! The route eases up a few moves before you clip the chains. Classic!
Climb up and left through the roof.  Pumping off the slopers at the top is fun.
The route left of the warm up.

12 short but fun sport climbs right on the lake. Good limestone with rating from 5.11a - 5.13a and go for 25-30ft. Some routes have permanent draws. Private property above so don't top out.  

  If your looking for solitude look somewhere else. Boats stop to watch frequently.
